To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The aggregate list of discovered apps on City-owned devices enrolled in Microsoft Intune mobile device management in CSV format. You can find instructions on how to export this list here:
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/mem/intune/apps/app-discovered-apps#monitor-discovered-apps-with-intune

Please select "Export the discovered apps raw data set" when asked.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

title: FBI Zebra Killings / Death Angels Records

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any FBI records created between October 1973 and August 1975 by the San Francisco office or headquarters regarding the “Zebra Killings” and/or the “Death Angels” cult of Nation of Islam (NOI) members allegedly or actually involved. 
2. Any FBI records of the joint / special task force formed at the behest of Mayor Alioto, compromised of San Francisco law enforcement authorities, the California Department of Justice, and the FBI regarding the hunt for the Zebra killers. 
3. Any FBI memo or report created between 1971 and 1975 concerning the San Francisco NOI Temple located in the Fillmore.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Andrew Free
